      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study yielded GCI of 3.1% for area-averaged wall shear stress and 4.7% for integrated NIH between medium (5.8M) and fine (14.3M) meshes. Both values satisfy the 5% acceptance criterion. Medium mesh used for all production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) match computational boundary conditions within ±5%.",
      "rationale": "PIV and hemolysis experiments conducted at 37°C with bovine blood analog (glycerin-water, viscosity 3.2 mPa·s). CFD boundary conditions set to match measured inlet flow rate and rotational speed. Deviation in fluid viscosity < 2% relative to experimental value."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted NIH within 25% of in-vitro measured mean; predicted velocity field within 10% mean absolute error.",
      "rationale": "NIH prediction within 18% of in-vitro mean at nominal operating condition. Velocity field mean absolute error 7.9% across PIV measurement planes. Both metrics satisfy acceptance criteria."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
