    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 requirements. Validation results demonstrate adequate agreement between CFD predictions and experimental data for velocity field and hemolysis index at conditions representative of the COU. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model is standard in the field and has been validated against in-vitro data within the COU operating envelope. The credibility assessment team concludes that the model is sufficiently credible to support the COU decision at the Medium assurance level.",
